\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. P. prostrata} Labill.,{\i  Icon. Pl. Syr.}{\b  1}: 15 (1791). Low, spreading shrub up to 1 m, with deflexed-arcuate branches. Young twigs puberulent. Leaves 9-12(-27) × 3-6(-9) mm, linear-oblong to broadly elliptical-ovate or -obovate, conspicuously incise-serrate at least in apical half, glabrous above, grey-tomentose to glabrous beneath. Flowers mostly solitary, sub-sessile, appearing before the leaves; hypanthium tubular; petals c. 7 mm, bright pink. Fruit c. 8 mm, broadly ovoid, red; endocarp slightly sulcate.{\i  Mountains of Mediterranean region; local.} Al Co Cr Gr Hs Ju Sa.
