\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. P. fruticosa} Pallas,{\i  Fl. Ross. }{\b 1}({\b 1}): 19 (1784) ({\i Cerasus fruticosa }(Pallas) Woronow). Low, spreading shrub 0·3-1·5 m (rarely more), completely glabrous. Leaves of long shoots 3-5·5 × 1·5-2·7 cm, elliptic-oblanceolate, finely crenate-serrate, dark, shining green; those of short shoots 1·5-2·5 cm, obovate, otherwise similar. Flowers in subsessile umbels of 2-5, with leaf-like bud-scales at the base; pedicels 2-3 cm. Hypanthium campanulate; petals 5-7 mm, white. Fruit 7-10 mm, globose, dark red; endocarp, smooth.{\i  Thickets and dry grassland. E., S.E. & C. Europe, northwards to} c. 57°{\i  in E. Russia, southwards to Bulgaria and Crna Gora, and westwards to W. Germany. }Au Bu Cz Ge Hu It Po Rm Rs(C, W, E).
